.bytes:[<!DOCTYPE html><html lang="ug"><head>  <meta charset="UTF-8">  <title>25 Uyghur Wisdoms</title>  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Amiri&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">  <style>    body {      font-family: 'Amiri', serif;      background-color: #fcf9f3;      padding: 30px;      line-height: 1.9;      color: #222;      direction: rtl;    }    .center {      text-align: center;      margin: 35px 0 10px;      font-size: 1.4em;      color: #2c3e50;    }    strong {      color: #111;    }    .wisdom-block {      margin-bottom: 40px;    }  </style></head><body>  <div class="wisdom-block">    <div class="center"><strong>1. ئەقىللىق كىشى بىر گەپتە چۈشىنىدۇ</strong></div>    <strong>English:</strong> A wise person understands with one word.<br>    <strong>Explanation:</strong> Intelligent people grasp meaning quickly, without needing long explanations.  </div>  <div class="wisdom-block">    <div class="center"><strong>2. كۆپ ئۈگەنگەن كۆپ بىلىدۇ</strong></div>    <strong>English:</strong> The one who learns more knows more.<br>    <strong>Explanation:</strong> Knowledge comes from continuous learning and curiosity.  </div>  <div class="wisdom-block">    <div class="center"><strong>3. ئادەمگە ئۆزىدىن ياخشى دوست بولمايدۇ</strong></div>    <strong>English:</strong> No one is a better friend to a person than themselves.<br>    <strong>Explanation:</strong> Self-reliance and self-care are the foundations of well-being.  </div>  <div class="wisdom-block">    <div class="center"><strong>4. خاتالىقتىن ئۆگىنىش ئەقىلنىڭ بېرىكىسى</strong></div>    <strong>English:</strong> Learning from mistakes is the wealth of wisdom.<br>    <strong>Explanation:</strong> Mistakes aren’t failures—they’re opportunities to grow wiser.  </div>  <div class="wisdom-block">    <div class="center"><strong>5. ئوقۇشقا خۇمار بولغان ئاقىل بولىدۇ</strong></div>    <strong>English:</strong> He who is passionate about learning becomes wise.<br>    <strong>Explanation:</strong> Passion and consistency in learning lead to true understanding.  </div>  <div class="wisdom-block">    <div class="center"><strong>6. ئالدى بىلەن دەسلەپكى قەدەم</strong></div>    <strong>English:</strong> First, take the first step.<br>    <strong>Explanation:</strong> Every journey starts with a small decision to move forward.  </div>  <div class="wisdom-block">    <div class="center"><strong>7. قانچى يۈگۈرسەڭمۇ، باشلىنىشسىز يېتىشەلمەيسەن</strong></div>    <strong>English:</strong> No matter how fast you run, without a start, you won’t arrive.<br>    <strong>Explanation:</strong> Action is meaningless without intention and beginnings.  </div>  <div class="wisdom-block">    <div class="center"><strong>8. ئۇقمايدىغانغا ئوقۇتما</strong></div>    <strong>English:</strong> Don’t teach those who won’t understand.<br>    <strong>Explanation:</strong> Some people aren’t ready to learn; save your energy.  </div>  <div class="wisdom-block">    <div class="center"><strong>9. ھەر كۈنى بىر قەدەم، مېڭىش جەريانى بولىدۇ</strong></div>    <strong>English:</strong> One step a day makes a journey.<br>    <strong>Explanation:</strong> Progress doesn’t need speed, only consistency.  </div>  <div class="wisdom-block">    <div class="center"><strong>10. زېھىن قەلەم بىلەن قۇدرەت تاپدۇ</strong></div>    <strong>English:</strong> The mind finds strength through the pen.<br>    <strong>Explanation:</strong> Writing, reading, and expressing thoughts strengthen intellect.  </div>  <!-- ... Continue for 11-25 ... --></body></html>];